 A man from Cameroon has accepted the call by President Volodymyr Zelensky of Ukraine for people from different countries to join the Ukrainian army and defend the country against Russia. A twitter user, @nzekiev shared photos of the man from Cameroon and wrote: “This is our friend who went to join the Ukraine army. He has been living here for long and he cherishes Ukraine. I am glad some of our people are supporting them. This is commendable.” This is our friend who went to join the Ukraine army. He has been living here for long and he cherishes Ukraine. I am glad some of our people are supporting them. This is commendable. pic.twitter.com/mxgdmSWPbt
— Nze (@nzekiev) March 1, 2022